### Input
Write a program that reverses a number.

### Example Input
654321

### Example Output
123456

### Solution

Reversing a number is a simple process. First, you convert a number to a string. Then, reverse the characters in the string. Finally, convert the characters back to an integer. This example does all those steps.

In this example, you enter the input integer. Then, you convert it so the number is in String format. You then use a Java method to reverse the characters. Finally, you do an integer literal conversion to convert the characters back to their integer values. The return integer value is not important. It just needs to be printed.

### Code
```
public class ReverseInt {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(reverseIntReverse(65432));
    }

    public static int reverseIntReverse(int num) {
        String number = String.valueOf(num);
        String reverse = new StringBuilder(number).reverse().toString();
        return new Integer(reverse);
    }
}
```

